TI  - Thermal Fatigue Failure of Low-Pressure Turbine Blade in a Low-Bypass Turbofan Engine
AU  - Mishra, R. K.
AU  - Jha, S. K.
T2  - Journal of Failure Analysis and Prevention
AB  - Failure of low-pressure (LP) turbine rotor blade in a low-bypass turbofan engine is analyzed to determine its root cause. Forensic and metallurgical investigations are carried out on the affected blades. High surface oxidation on damaged blade is found to be the reason for crack initiation in blades. Thermal fatigue is the probable cause of failure in the blades due to prolong operation at maximum condition and malfunction of engine control system.
