AB  - In striving to improve metrics, especially to lower fuel consumption, weight and cost, and to reduce noise and emissions, the jet engine manufacturers world wide are continuously looking for new concepts to introduce a step change in the turbofan engine development. One promising concept having been investigated for two decades is, to apply a speed reduction gear on the low spool of a two-shaft engine between the Fan on the one (slow spinning) side and the LPC and the LPT on the other (fast spinning) side, making the configuration geared compared to the direct drive turbofan. By means of de-coupling the Fan speed from the rest of the low spool turbo machinery the designer gains an additional degree of freedom which allows him to better optimize the turbo machines independently.
