AU  - Yin, K.
AU  - Lou, P.
AU  - He, D.
AU  - Bai, B.
T2  - Equipment Intelligent Operation and Maintenance
AB  - The lubrication system of aero-engine directly affects the system safety and reliability. Therefore, health monitoring and fault diagnosis are critical. In this study, a lubrication system simulation model aiming at engine health management is established using Modelica frame. In addition, 3-dimensional oil vane pump computational fluid dynamics (CFD) model is developed with the dedicated software PumpLinx. Multi-fidelity aero-engine lubrication system model, integrating the detailed pump model into the 1-dimensional lubrication system is established. Hereby, the assessment of component deteriorations in an overall system context is enabled, and the resulting impacts on the overall system are quantified for system monitoring purposes. This study demonstrates the capabilities of multi-fidelity simulation in the context of engine health monitoring.
